---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = 'Cookie Policy | Ads Calculator';
const description = 'Cookie Policy for Ads Calculator. Learn what cookies we use, why, and how you can manage or disable your preferences.';
const keywords = 'cookie policy, ads calculator cookies, manage cookies, analytics cookies, advertising cookies';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} keywords={keywords} lang="en">
  <main class="flex-grow py-12 sm:py-20 px-4 sm:px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white/80 dark:bg-slate-900/80 backdrop-blur-xl rounded-[2rem] shadow-2xl border border-white/20 dark:border-white/5 p-8 sm:p-12 animate-in fade-in slide-in-from-bottom-4 duration-1000">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2 tracking-tight">Cookie Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm mb-10">Last updated: June 2026</p>

      <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">1. What are Cookies?</h2>
          <p>Cookies are small text files that websites save to your computer or mobile device when you visit them. They are widely used to make websites work, or work more efficiently, as well as to provide reporting and marketing optimization statistics to the site owners.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">2. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
          <p>At Ads Calculator, we use cookies to personalize advertisements, analyze traffic, and ensure technical functionality. The cookies active on our Site fall into the following categories:</p>
          
          <div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
            <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
              <thead>
                <tr class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-900/80 text-slate-900 dark:text-white border-b border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
                  <th class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold">Cookie Name</th>
                  <th class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold">Provider</th>
                  <th class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold">Purpose</th>
                  <th class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold">Duration</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr class="border-b border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
                  <td class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">_ga, _ga_*</td>
                  <td class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">Google Analytics</td>
                  <td class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3">Tracks anonymous usage metrics and site visits.</td>
                  <td class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3">2 Years</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="bg-slate-50/50 dark:bg-slate-900/30 border-b border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
                  <td class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">_gcl_au</td>
                  <td class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">Google AdSense</td>
                  <td class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3">Tracks advertising conversions and campaign performance.</td>
                  <td class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3">3 Months</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
                  <td class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">DSID, IDE</td>
                  <td class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">Google DoubleClick</td>
                  <td class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3">Serves targeted ads based on prior user web browsing.</td>
                  <td class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3">1 Year</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="bg-slate-50/50 dark:bg-slate-900/30">
                  <td class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">GTM-*</td>
                  <td class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">Google Tag Manager</td>
                  <td class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3">Facilitates deployment of analytical scripts.</td>
                  <td class="border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 px-4 py-3">Session</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">3. How Can You Manage Cookies?</h2>
          <p>You have the absolute right to accept, configure, or refuse cookies. Most web browsers allow you to control cookies through their configuration settings. Disabling cookies might affect your experience and limit some technical functionalities of the Site.</p>
          <p>To configure your specific browser, visit the official guidelines:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li><a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">Google Chrome Help</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/cookies-information-websites-store-on-your-computer" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">Mozilla Firefox Help</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://support.apple.com/guide/safari/manage-cookies-sfri11471/mac" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">Apple Safari Help</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/delete-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">Microsoft Edge Help</a></li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">4. Opt-Out of Personalized Advertising</h2>
          <p>You can adjust your Google Ads settings and choose to opt out of interest-based ads. To opt-out across participating ad platforms, use these resources:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Configure Google Ads personalization preferences at: <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">Google Ad Personalization Settings</a>.</li>
            <li>Manage cookie personalization across diverse networks via: <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">Digital Advertising Alliance Opt-Out Page</a>.</li>
            <li>Opt-out through the Network Advertising Initiative: <a href="https://optout.networkadvertising.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">NAI Consumer Opt-Out Portal</a>.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">5. Policy Revisions</h2>
          <p>We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time in response to operational changes or legal requirements. We recommend reviewing this document regularly to remain informed about our cookie usage.</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
